{"lemma":"حاضِرُو","slug":"حاضِرُو","root":"ح.ض.ر","root_slug":"ح-ض-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ض-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حاضِر","root":"حضر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","intj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":20},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8324"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B6%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give a lecture to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lecture"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to witness, be present for"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to present one's self"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give (a ready answer)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sit with (someone) in contending or disputing"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to contend with, to dispute, to debate, to bandy words with (someone)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to plead a cause"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to converse with"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to vie in running"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dispute for a thing, win and carry it off"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to scourge, to beat, to whip"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"present, before the eyes, ready (also applied to money)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"second person","tags":["second-person"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the present tense"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"settled, domiciled"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inhabitant of a village of town"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"family"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tribe"},{"pos":"intj","gloss":"Used to affirm a command.","tags":["dialectal"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of حَضَرَ (ḥaḍara, “to be present, to be settled”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8324","headword_ar":"حَاضِرٌ","root":"HDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"present:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) pl. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADiruwna","text_ar":"حَاضِرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuD~arN","text_ar":"حُضَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [more commonly]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuDuwrN","text_ar":"حُضُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) which last is originally an inf. n. (S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotuhu wafulaAnN HaADirN","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُهُ وَفُلَانٌ حَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did it such a one being present."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawa mino HaADiriY Almaliki","text_ar":"هَوَ مِنْ حَاضِرِى المَلِكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of those who are in the presence of the king"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  So, too, applied to a time: and you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApu HaADirapN","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةُ حَاضِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqotuhaA HaADirN","text_ar":"وَقْتُهَا حَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time of prayer is come."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-  [Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ready,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared:"},{"kind":"text","text":"often used in this sense in the lexicons &c., as in modern Arabic. See 4.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwluwA maA","text_ar":"قُولُوا مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa HaADirN Einodakumo","text_ar":"هُوَ حَاضِرٌ عِنْدَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Say ye what is ready with you"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in your minds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa HaADirN","text_ar":"هُوَ حَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAljawaAbi","text_ar":"بِالجَوَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is ready with the answer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reply"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAln~awaAdiri","text_ar":"بِالنَّوَادِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with rare words"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressions"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaDurN","text_ar":"حَضُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) which latter word, alone, signifies a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the quality of perspicuity of speech, and intelligence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw AlbayaAni","text_ar":"ذُو البَيَانِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlfiqohi","text_ar":"وَالفِقْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A visiting angel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADirapN","text_ar":"حَاضِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a class"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of visiting angels"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming to a region, district,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, of cities, towns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages, and of cultivated land; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdK","text_ar":"بَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHotaDirN","text_ar":"مُحْتَضِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b6-  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staying, residing, dwelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bamawoDiEK","text_ar":"بَمَوْضِعٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b7-  [A man, or people,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelling, by water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdK","text_ar":"بَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuDuwrN","text_ar":"حُضُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuD~aArN","text_ar":"حُضَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaDarapN","text_ar":"حَضَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA EalaY AlmaA='i","text_ar":"مَا عَلَى المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADirN","text_ar":"حَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not any one staying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelling, by the water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i qawomN HuD~aArN","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ قَوْمٌ حُضَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaADiru","text_ar":"مَحَاضِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoDarN","text_ar":"مَحْضَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", a syn. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaADirN","text_ar":"خَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are a people staying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelling, by water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADirN","text_ar":"حَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies any people"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that have alighted and taken up their abode by a constant source of water, and do not remove from it in winter nor in summer, whether they have alighted and taken up their abode in towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages, and cultivated land, and houses of clay, or pitched their tents by the water, and remained there, and sustained their beasts with the water and herbage around them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N HaADirN","text_ar":"حَىٌّ حَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tribe that has alighted and is abiding by a constant source of water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADirapN","text_ar":"حَاضِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADiruwna","text_ar":"حَاضِرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a people staying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelling, by waters; alighting there in the hottest time of summer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when the weather becomes cool, they migrate from the constant sources of water, and go into the desert, seeking the vicinity of herbage; and then they are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiyapN","text_ar":"بَادِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAduwna","text_ar":"بَادُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bdw","text_ar":"بدو"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great tribe"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tribe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when staying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelling, in the abode which is their place of assembling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADirapN","text_ar":"حَاضِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaADiru TaY~i'K","text_ar":"حَاضِرُ طَىِّءٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The great tribe of Teiyi."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) It is a pl., (S,) or coll. n., (ISd,) [or quasipl. n.,] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmirN","text_ar":"سَامِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAj~N","text_ar":"حَاجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, ISd) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sum~aArN","text_ar":"سُمَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~aAjN","text_ar":"حُجَّاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)       -A3-  Also, of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place where people are present;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where people stay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwell, by waters:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnN maHoDuwrN","text_ar":"مَكَانٌ مَحْضُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazalonaA HaADira baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"نَزَلْنَا حَاضِرَ بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We alighted and took up our abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sojourned, at the place where the sons of such a one were present;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were staying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelling, by waters"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (El-Khat- tábee.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoDarN","text_ar":"مَحْضَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["A","K","S","TA","T","ISd","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}